item.title: Hole in fuel hose caused fire in Cathay Pacific A350 flight, Hong Kong probe finds
item.description: A Cathay Pacific Airbus A350 encountered a fire caused by a ruptured fuel hose, leading to an emergency return to Hong Kong. The incident raised concerns about engine reliability and prompted inspections of 15 other aircraft in the fleet. Recommendations were issued for Rolls-Royce to provide inspection requirements for the affected components.
